<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>RECONDITIONING ROTORS - TROUBLESHOOTING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>TROUBLESHOOTING</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
            <title>TROUBLESHOOTING CHART</title>
            <table id="t0401801">
                <title>Troubleshooting Chart</title>
                <tgroup cols="3" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="1.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="1.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="3.75in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>CONDITION</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>CAUSE</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>REMEDY</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Brakes squeal during application.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Lateral runout.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Check rotor surface with a dial indicator. Refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="t0401801">LATERAL RUNOUT</hotlnk>. A less serious condition may be
                                    corrected by resurfacing the rotor to allowable tolerances. Excessive lateral runout
                                    requires replacing the rotor.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Improperly installed brake pads.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Check the lining for the proper friction rating. If incorrect, replace with the
                                    proper brake pads.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Rotor is polished.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Remove the gloss with 80-grit emery cloth.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Brake pads are glazed.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Remove the glaze on the brake pads with a file.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Roughness or chatter during brake application.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Parallelism or variation in rotor thickness.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Check rotor for uneven surface areas. Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s04018w_25.xml" xrefid="t0401802">PARALLELISM OR VARIATION IN
                                        THICKNESS</hotlnk>. If the condition is not too serious, resurface the rotor. If
                                    surface variance is excessive or if the condition persists, replace the rotor.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Lateral runout.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Check rotor surface with a dial indicator. Refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="t0401801">LATERAL RUNOUT</hotlnk>. A less serious condition may be
                                    corrected by resurfacing the rotor to allowable tolerances. Excessive lateral runout
                                    requires replacing the rotor.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Cracked rotor.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the rotor.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
